CHANGES
=======

Unreleased
----------

* Make the Windows PowerShell installer stay on the native PowerShell path even
when Git Bash, curl, or tar are present on PATH.
* Use Windows' built-in `tar.exe` explicitly from PowerShell and generated
`lintconfig.cjs` updater paths.
* Avoid double-running the PowerShell installer when it is loaded via
`Invoke-WebRequest ... | Invoke-Expression`.
* Delegate `install.sh` to the PowerShell installer when it is run from Git
Bash/MSYS/Cygwin on Windows.
* Default installers to the latest GitHub release and add `--latest` /
`-Latest` to override pinned environment configuration.
* Avoid assigning to PowerShell's read-only `$IsWindows` automatic variable in
PowerShell 7.
* Make generated `lintconfig` scripts retain the install-time config flags
while still updating from the latest installer archive.

Version 1.0.42 (2026-03-19)
---------------------------

* Fix `.vue` parse errors when Vue support is not active by ignoring `.vue`
files unless the Vue stack is installed.
* Add missing package metadata fields and sync changelog version line for repo
check compliance.
* Update the installer release workflow to declare `actions/setup-node@v6` on
Node 24 for repo policy compliance.

Version 1.0.41 (2026-02-22)
---------------------------

* Bump bundled installer/default version references from `1.0.40` to `1.0.41`.

Version 1.0.40 (2026-02-22)
---------------------------

* Bump bundled installer/default version references from `1.0.39` to `1.0.40`.

Version 1.0.39 (2026-02-22)
---------------------------

* Make generated script chaining package-manager agnostic via `npm-run-all`
(`run-s`).
* Replace `rm -rf` in generated `cleanbuild` with cross-platform `rimraf`.
* Bump compatible lint/tooling dependency versions (keep ESLint v9 and
`jsonc-eslint-parser` v2 for compatibility).
* On Windows, prefer running `install.sh` through `bash` when `bash` + `curl` +
`tar` are available; fall back to PowerShell installer flow.

Version 1.0.38 (2026-02-07)
---------------------------

* When Markdown is enabled (`--md`), lint `.md` files via `@eslint/markdown` and include them in lint scripts.

Version 1.0.37 (2026-02-07)
---------------------------

* Bump Stylelint to 17.1.1 (installer + dev deps).
* Drop deprecated eslint-plugin-markdown (Markdown is formatting-only).
* Add root eslint.config.mjs and align lint scripts with installer defaults.

Version 1.0.36 (2026-02-02)
---------------------------

* Ignore nested dist/node_modules and Nuxt build output directories.

Version 1.0.35 (2026-02-02)
---------------------------

* Enforce tabs with tabWidth 4 in shipped Prettier and VSCode defaults.

Version 1.0.34 (2026-02-02)
---------------------------

* Accept --version=<v> style in install.sh.

Version 1.0.33 (2026-02-02)
---------------------------

* Bump lint/tooling dependencies to current versions.
* Add --vue/--no-vue switch (default auto-detect) to installers and updater.
* Update README install commands to be runnable as-is with explicit defaults.

Version 1.0.32 (2025-12-31)
---------------------------

* Add lintconfig updater script and script target to refresh installer config
later.
* Switch installer flags to --md/--no-md and default CSS to off (unknown option
warning).
* Bump ESLint/Prettier/TypeScript ESLint/Vue lint deps to current versions.

Version 1.0.31 (2025-12-02)
---------------------------

* Add Stylelint VSCode settings and extension recommendation when CSS/SCSS
linting is enabled (remove them when disabled).

Version 1.0.30 (2025-11-28)
---------------------------

* Prefer `.prettierrc`: migrate existing `.prettierrc.json` into `.prettierrc`,
remove duplicates, and add defaults when none exist.

Version 1.0.29 (2025-11-28)
---------------------------

* If only .prettierrc.json is extracted (no existing .prettierrc), keep it and
write defaults; if both exist, keep .prettierrc and drop the duplicate JSON.

Version 1.0.28 (2025-11-28)
---------------------------

* Preserve existing `.prettierrc` by removing the installer's `.prettierrc.json`
when both are present after extraction.

Version 1.0.27 (2025-11-28)
---------------------------

* When both `.prettierrc` and `.prettierrc.json` exist after install, prefer
`.prettierrc.json` and remove the duplicate `.prettierrc`.

Version 1.0.26 (2025-11-28)
---------------------------

* When CSS is disabled, installers also delete any extracted
`stylelint.config.cjs` to keep configs clean.

Version 1.0.25 (2025-11-28)
---------------------------

* When CSS linting is disabled via flags, remove `stylelint.config.cjs` and
prune stylelint deps/scripts.

Version 1.0.24 (2025-11-28)
---------------------------

* Switch Markdown handling to formatting only (no ESLint code-block linting) and
add optional install flags via install.sh/install.ps1.

Version 1.0.23 (2025-11-27)
---------------------------

* Expand default ESLint ignores to cover .netlify and .nuxt build artifacts
(including nested installs) and clean redundant patterns.

Version 1.0.22 (2025-11-25)
---------------------------

* Add Prettier prose wrapping defaults (80 columns) to the installer templates
for Markdown.

Version 1.0.21 (2025-11-25)
---------------------------

* Make the installed lint scripts tolerate projects without CSS/SCSS/Markdown by
adding `--allow-empty-input` and `--no-error-on-unmatched-pattern`.

Version 1.0.20 (2025-11-24)
---------------------------

* Add markdown linting support and include CSS/SCSS via Stylelint in the
installer scripts/config (keeping dist/.output/node_modules ignored).

Version 1.0.19 (2025-11-11)
---------------------------

* Fix `installer/eslint.config.mjs` import order so the config linting rules
pass without manual overrides.

Version 1.0.18 (2025-11-11)
---------------------------

* Prevent Vue-specific lint dependencies from triggering Vue mode detection (so
TS-only projects drop the Vue stack again).

Version 1.0.17 (2025-11-11)
---------------------------

* Installer now detects Vue/Nuxt dependencies and installs/removes the
framework-specific ESLint stack automatically, pruning any extra
eslint/prettier packages it finds.
* ESLint config dynamically loads Vue presets only when present, scopes them to
`.vue` files, and drops the eslint-plugin-prettier bridge in favor of native
Prettier formatting plus VSCode defaults.
* Added workspace `.vscode` settings/extensions so ESLint + Prettier work out of
the box after installing the recommended extensions.

Version 1.0.16 (2025-09-27)
---------------------------

* Bump ESLint ecosystem to latest compatible releases (ESLint 9.36, Prettier
3.6, TypeScript ESLint 8.44, Vue plugins, importer resolver).
* Add jsonc-eslint-parser and relax TypeScript lint rules so JSON/package.json
files lint cleanly.
* Extend lint coverage for .cjs/.mjs files, align lint/format scripts with the
new extensions, and reformat configure-eslint installer script with prettier
compatible tabs.
* Regenerate installer dependency list to match published versions while leaving
bundle creation to CI.
* Verified installer flow in a sample project (`npm run lintfix`, `npm run
lint`).
* Re-enabled `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` and
`@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars` as warnings.
